item.name: Paging Memory free
item.description: Available paging memory (in megabytes). A -1 will be returned if this value could not be determined.

item.name: Paging Memory size
item.description: Total virtual memory available from the OS (in megabytes). A -1 will be returned if this value could not be determined

trigger.name: Paging memory utilization is high on {HOST.HOST}

item.name: Physical Memory free
item.description: The amount of free physical memory (in megabytes). A -1 will be returned if this value could not be determined.

item.name: Physical Memory size
item.description: Total amount of physical memory as seen by the OS (in megabytes). A -1 will be returned if this value could not be determined.

trigger.name: Physical memory utilization is high on {HOST.HOST}

item.name: Device form factor
item.description: The form factor of the system. Setting this variable to unknown will fail.

item.name: Device hood status
item.description:
The status of the chassis intrusion alert hardware and the hood presence
unknown(1) - unable to determine the system intrusion alert hardware presence not-installed(2) - system intrusion alert hardware not installed hood-ok(3) - system intrusion alert hardware is installed the hood cover is seated properly hood-removed(4) - system intrusion alert hardware is installed but the hood cover is removed

item.name: Device TPM module status
item.description: This field will be populated if TPM module is present in the system board. other(1) No record of TPM exist. absent(2) TPM module is not present in the system. presentEnabled(3) TPM module is present in the system and currently enabled. presentDisabled(4) TPM module is present in the system and currently not enabled.

item_prototype.name: {#SNMPINDEX} - ioBoard temperature threshold
item_prototype.description:
This is the shutdown threshold temperature sensor setting in degrees celsius. This is the temperature in which the sensor will be considered to be in a failed state thus causing the system to be shutdown.
If this value cannot be determined by software, then a value of -1 will be returned.
